  "prompt": "Is 291 a good score in gre?",
  "response": "A score of 291 on the GRE (Graduate Record Examination) is considered below average. The GRE is divided into three sections: Verbal Reasoning, Quantitative Reasoning, and Analytical Writing. Typically, scores range from 130 to 170 for the Verbal and Quantitative sections, and from 0 to 6 for the Analytical Writing section. \n\nIf you scored 291 combined in the Verbal and Quantitative sections, it suggests that you might need improvement to be competitive for most graduate programs. Many reputable programs often look for scores in the range of 300-320 or higher. However, the importance of your GRE score can vary depending on the institution and program to which you are applying. Some programs may place a heavier emphasis on other aspects of your application, such as your undergraduate GPA, letters of recommendation, work experience, and personal statement. Always check the specific requirements for each program to understand how your score fits into their admissions criteria.",
